sub_title: Relationship Building and Project/Program Management for Business Growth and Development in Tech & Innovation | Business Trainer, Facilitator, Coach ICF | Creative, Resilient | Open for challenging role in NL or remotely
summary:
Extensive international experience and track record in all sides of B2B Communications in Tech and Innovation field: from Partnerships and Business Development to Event Management, Community Building, Employer Brand, International Relations, GR, PR and Storytelling.

I am a highly-skilled organiser, project manager, relationship builder and mentor that has a passion for finding and connecting business to opportunities and new markets.
Communications is one of my biggest strengths, and I am a published author.

In my lifetime, I was featured in media many times with my articles, personal and professional accomplishments or expert comments, including Wall Street Journal and BBC.

I lived, worked and studied in Europe, North America, Ukraine, and had clients in the USA, UK and globally.

I used to work in leadership roles in small and medium size companies with multicultural environment where I had to combine strategic thinking and execution. In particular, I built and run the country office of British marketing company GROWTH SHOP. Helped to develop the acceleration hub Sector X in the innovation park UNIT city, and brought on board clients like L'Oréal, British American Tobacco and more. Helped startups raise $500K+ in pre-seed round. Besides, I also have entrepreneurial experience.

Business Trainer & Facilitator, Coach ICF.

To name just a few projects I was involved in:

- Hackathon Facilitator - European Design Upgrade, 2020, 2021 (EU-funded)
- Mentor - Diamond Challenge for High School Entrepreneurs, 2020 (USA-funded)
- Facilitator - Social Impact Award (SIA) Summit, 2019 (organised by Austria-based organisation)
- Trainer - Erasmus training course "Empowering youth entrepreneurship in rural areas”, 2019 (EU-funded)
- Pitch Coach - Unit School of Business, 2019-2021 (Ukraine)
- Faculty Instructor - British Columbia Institute of Technology, School of Business, 2016-2017 (Canada)

Alumna of prestigious scholarships in Canada, Sweden, Norway and Ukraine: Ukrainian Canadian Congress Parliamentary Program, Swedish Institute Visby Program & Network for Future Global Leaders (it was rebranded to SI Network for Global Professionals), ISS at University of Oslo and Victor Pinchuk Zavtra.UA Program.

Top 1% in LinkedIn Industry SSI Rank (Social Selling Index).

My Top-10 Gallup CliftonStrengths:

1. Strategic
2. Futuristic (= visionary)
3. Activator (= doer)
4. Connectedness (= dot connector)
5. Relator (= relationship builder)
6. Intellection
7. Maximiser (= I love building projects from 0 to excellence and fame)
8. Responsibility
9. Deliberative
10. Ideation
